        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 5:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It should be noted that the great command of the gospel is set forth in the Sermon on the Plain in its width and universality, without being formally contrasted with the Pharisaic gloss, “Thou shalt love thy neighbour, and hate thine enemy,” as in the Sermon on the Mount.",
